article.description: Clide Geffrard scored 20 points and grabbed eight rebounds as Stephen F. Austin beat Southeastern Louisiana 89-69 Monday night.
article.headline: Stephen F. Austin buries Southeastern Louisiana 89-69
article.linkText: Stephen F. Austin buries Southeastern Louisiana 89-69
article.story: HAMMOND, La. -- Clide Geffrard scored 20 points and grabbed eight rebounds as Stephen F. Austin beat Southeastern Louisiana 89-69 Monday night. Geffrard's jumper with 12:52 to play in the first half gave Stephen F. Austin (9-5, 2-0 Southland) a 19-9 lead before Southeastern Louisiana rallied to cut the deficit to 22-19 on Marlain Veal's layup. But Geffrard's followed with a 3 and Thomas Walkup hit back-to-back jumpers to move the lead to 29-19. Leading 43-33 at the half, the Lumberjacks used a 10-3 run to start the half and were never again challenged. The Lumberjacks now own a nine-game conference win streak and are 37-1 against conference opponents under coach Brad Underwood. It was Stephen F. Austin's first road win of the season. Zay Jackson led Southeastern Louisiana (2-12, 0-1) with 14 points. Veal scored 11 with six assists.
